.TH "fc_exch_mgr_reset" 9 "fc_exch_mgr_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_exch_mgr_reset \- Reset all EMs of a local port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fc_exch_mgr_reset
.BI "(struct fc_lport *lport "  ","
.BI "u32 sid "  ","
.BI "u32 did "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lport" 12
The local port whose EMs are to be reset
.IP "sid" 12
The source ID
.IP "did" 12
The destination ID
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reset all EMs associated with a given local port. Release all
sequences and exchanges. If sid is non-zero then reset only the
exchanges sent from the local port's FID. If did is non-zero then
reset only exchanges destined for the local port's FID.
